         <div type="memoir">
            <head>Rosine Taneberger</head>
            <div type="page" n="1">
               <head>Page 1 <seg ana="MemBeth_0140-01" />
               </head>
               <p> 
                  II. The married Sist. <persName>Rosine Taneberger</persName>. 
                  She was Ao <date>1708</date> born at <placeName>Mammendorf in Moravia</placeName>.
                  Her Vaters name was <persName>Geo. Weber</persName>. The holy
                  ghost had from her tender youth his work in
                  heart &amp; she spent her time continually  
                  without Rest in her soul. In her 25th. year
                  of Age she married <persName>Michel Taneberger</persName>. she
                  [has] 2 Boys with him but they died very young. She 
                  very often pineth to hear the Gospel of <persName>Jesus</persName>
                  Sufferings of Death, therefore she very begged dear
                  <abbr>God</abbr> to still her Desire &amp; help her to a Place where
                  she could find rest for her poor soul,then she could
                  not find that in her <placeName>Mother Country</placeName>. Ao <date>1753. the 13th October</date>
                  She got a feeling in her heart to move to <placeName>Gnaden-
                     frey</placeName>, they hastened as much as possible &amp; escaped
                  hardly from their pursuers. <date>The 31 of Dec.</date>
                  she arrived here very much rejoiced. Soon after
                  a critical occasion pretty nearly persuadeth
                  her husbands to remove from here to his son.
                  She therefore was so embarrassed &amp; intreated our 
                  <persName>Serviour</persName> in her Perplexity saying: feared my heart catched a spark 
                  of grace, &amp; instead to become a fire he will be quenched!                  
               </p>
